### Test cases for UserManagementAPI
### The API uses custom token validation in Program.cs.
### Missing/invalid Authorization headers return 401 Unauthorized with a JSON body like { "error": "Unauthorized." }.

### 1) Get users without auth -> expect 401 Unauthorized
GET http://localhost:5165/users

### 2) Get users with wrong token -> expect 401 Unauthorized
GET http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Bearer wrong-token

### 3) Get users with wrong auth scheme -> expect 401 Unauthorized
GET http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Token secret-token

### 4) Get users with valid token -> expect 200 OK and a list of users
GET http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Bearer secret-token

### 5) Get a non-existent user with valid token -> expect 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:5165/users/999
Authorization: Bearer secret-token

### 6) Create a user with valid data -> expect 201 Created
POST http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Charlie Brown",
  "email": "charlie@example.com"
}

### 7) Create a user with invalid email -> expect 400 Bad Request
POST http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid User",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

### 8) Create a user without a request body -> expect 400 Bad Request
POST http://localhost:5165/users
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
Content-Type: application/json

### 9) Update an existing user with valid data -> expect 200 OK
PUT http://localhost:5165/users/1
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Updated",
  "email": "alice.updated@example.com"
}

### 10) Update a non-existent user -> expect 404 Not Found
PUT http://localhost:5165/users/999
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost User",
  "email": "ghost@example.com"
}

### 11) Delete an existing user -> expect 204 No Content
DELETE http://localhost:5165/users/1
Authorization: Bearer secret-token

### 12) Delete a non-existent user -> expect 404 Not Found
DELETE http://localhost:5165/users/999
Authorization: Bearer secret-token
